{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDM3MDYxMzk0", "number": 1685, "title": "Allow instructors to enable / disable automatic assessment proposals", "bodyText": "Checklist\n\n I tested all changes and all related features with different users (student, tutor, instructor, admin) on the test server https://artemistest.ase.in.tum.de.\n\nMotivation and Context\nAutomatic assessment proposals have been activated automatically for UML class and activity diagrams.\nDescription\nNow, instructors can also choose to deactivate it for those two types. All other types are not supported yet. I also cleaned up some outdated code\nSteps for Testing\n\nCreate / edit a modeling exercises\nTry out different diagram types\nTry out different options for Automatic assessment suggestions enabled\nCheck that these values are saved correctly by choosing edit again\nParticipate in the exercises with 2 student accounts (having similar submissions)\nAssess the first submission and check whether the 2nd has some automatic suggestions (depending on the exercise configuration)\n\nLegacy exercises have a null value for the attribute assessment_type. If this won't be changed to true/false, the old behavior is preserved (this was already implemented on the server side before this PR)", "createdAt": "2020-06-19T11:59:12Z", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1685", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "29bab4b6225dc4243f170bd9d31c1ae0a5db74d9"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-06-22T18:05:02Z", "author": {"login": "krusche"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 4, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcsxsyUgH2gAyNDM3MDYxMzk0OjAxMDdiYTU0N2Y2MzM0ZjVlODI0NTRiODNjNDRjMDY0MWFlYjBlOTY=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABctyFh3AFqTQzNTAwNDE2Mw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "0107ba547f6334f5e82454b83c44c0641aeb0e96", "author": {"user": null}, "url": "https://github.